title: CFMEU investigated over corruption in Qld

title: Study finds fish oil can prevent preterm births
description: A study out of South Australia has discovered that omega-3 fatty acids found in fish oil can prevent preterm births by up to 42 per cent. #study #fishoil #birth #pregnancy #research

title: Mexico City protests turn violent

title: Melbourne restaurant fire forces mass evacuation | 7NEWS
description: A fire broke out at an Indian restaurant in Melbourne's Essendon at around 5am, forcing the evacuation of more than 100 residents. The blaze started in the kitchen but was successfully contained to the business premises. Buckley Street was closed in both directions while fire fighters assessed damage and conducted cleanup operations. title: Cervical cancer screening saves lives | 7NEWS
description: Cervical cancer claims the lives of more than 250 Australian women annually, with doctors reporting concerning numbers of women missing vital screening tests. Dr Nim Cabraal, a gynaecological oncologist from the Mater in Brisbane, explains that shame and embarrassment about cervical screening, along with lack of health awareness, are key barriers preventing women from getting tested. Early detection through regular screening can identify precancerous conditions during the five to ten year precancerous period, allowing for simple outpatient treatments that prevent cancer development with 95% success rates.
